Class ProviderDelegate

java.lang.Object
  sorcer.core.provider.ProviderDelegate
All Implemented Interfaces:
SorcerConstants
public class ProviderDelegate
extends Object
implements SorcerConstants

The provider delegate implements most of the intialization and configuration of service providers by dependency injection.

getAttributes

public Entry[] getAttributes()
Creates the service attributes to be used with Jini lookup services.

This function will create the following entries:

  • A Name.
  • A SorcerServiceInfoentry with all the information about this provider.
  • A main UIDescriptor if the provider overrides
  • Extra lookup attributes set via #addExtraLookupAttribute(Entry) ServiceProvider.getMainUIDescriptor().

Returns:
an array of Jini Service Entries.
Throws:
ConfigurationException

getProxy

public Object getProxy()
Returns a proxy object for this provider. If the smart proxy is allocated then returns a non exported object to be registered with loookup services. However, if a smart proxy implements Outer then the provider's proxy is set as its inner proxy. Otherwise the Remote outer proxy of this provider is returned.

Returns:
a proxy, or null
See Also:
Provider.getProxy()
